  {
    "ts": "2026-06-19T03:57:49+00:00",
    "headline": "India's Nifty IT index at three-year low as bellwether Accenture flags weak outlook",
    "summary": "India's Nifty IT index fell to a three-year low on Friday after bellwether Accenture forecast quarterly sales below Wall ‌Street view, cut its annual revenue outlook and reported softer bookings in ‌its managed services business. Shares of Indian IT companies, including TCS, Infosys, and HCLTech fell 4% to 8% ​after Accenture flagged deal delays and a $400 million hit to its Middle East business from the Iran conflict. India's $315 billion IT sector faces concerns that AI could disrupt its labour-intensive model, while geopolitical and economic uncertainty weighs on demand as clients defer non-essential tech ‌spending.",
    "url": "https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/stocks/articles/indian-stocks-tumble-bellwether-accenture-035749702.html",
    "source": "Reuters",
    "provider": "yfinance",
    "raw": {
      "id": "1f2e948a-ed05-369b-b1fa-8c74a0b16eee",
      "content": {
        "id": "1f2e948a-ed05-369b-b1fa-8c74a0b16eee",
        "contentType": "STORY",
        "title": "India's Nifty IT index at three-year low as bellwether Accenture flags weak outlook",
        "description": "",
        "summary": "India's Nifty IT index fell to a three-year low on Friday after bellwether Accenture forecast quarterly sales below Wall ‌Street view, cut its annual revenue outlook and reported softer bookings in ‌its managed services business. Shares of Indian IT companies, including TCS, Infosys, and HCLTech fell 4% to 8% ​after Accenture flagged deal delays and a $400 million hit to its Middle East business from the Iran conflict. India's $315 billion IT sector faces concerns that AI could disrupt its labour-intensive model, while geopolitical and economic uncertainty weighs on demand as clients defer non-essential tech ‌spending.",
